node.text:
These #fritters are so creamy that you will forget your usual pancakes!

INGREDIENTS
250g (1 cup) cottage cheese
10g (2 tsp) vanilla sugar
50g (¼ cup) sugar
180ml (¾ cup) milk
25ml (2 tbsp) oil
2 eggs
150g (1 1/5 cups) flour
5g (1 tsp) baking powder
Apricot jam

METHOD
Add cheese, milk, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla sugar, oil to a mixing bowl. Whisk the mixture. Add flour and baking powder. Stir.
Whisk the egg whites and salt with a mixer and mix with the previous mixture.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Fill with jam. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

node.text:
Quick and delicious!

INGREDIENTS
220ml (1 cup) yogurt
150g (1 1/4 cup) flour
1 egg
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp soda
1/2 tsp salt
200g minced meat
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
2 tbsp shredded parmesan

METHOD
In a bowl mix together yogurt, egg and spices, add in flour.
In another bowl mix together meat with salt, pepper and Parmesan.
Into the pan on medium heat add a tablespoon of prepared mixture top it with meat and another tablespoon of the mixture.
Fry from both sides.

This method is genius! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
 300g (2 cups) all-purpose flour;
 60g (¼ cup) butter, melted;
 100ml (⅓ cup+2 tbsp) water;
 Cornstarch.
 
METHOD
 Combine water, melted butter and flour to form a smooth dough.
 Set the dough aside for 20 minutes then roll into a thin rectangle and dust with cornstarch generously.
 Fold as shown on the video and repeat once more.
 Set the dough aside for 20 minutes then roll out thinly and cut into circles.
 Fold each circle and pinch with a clothing pin. Fry, dipping in hot oil, until the dough ‘blooms’, then remove the toothpick and cook until golden

This method to cook eggs is genius! You've never seen anything like this!

INGREDIENTS
250g (2 cups) flour
1 tsp salt
120ml (2/3 cup) water
4 tbsp oil
100 g melted butter
6 eggs

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, oil, salt and flour. Let the dough rest for 30 minutes. Divide the dough into 6 pieces and roll out each.
Spread with melted butter and roll the dough. Roll out again for a little. Fry it in the pan on medium heat adding the egg into each bread.

node.text:
Ever tried to fry pasta? You'll fall in love with this recipe! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Paccheri pasta
Ricotta
Cooked ham
Provolone
Parmesan
3 eggs
Breadcrumbs
Salt
Pepper
Oil

METHOD
Boil the pasta for 10 minutes and let it cool.
Mix ricotta, diced ham, cheese, salt, pepper, and parmesan in a bowl. Place the mixture in a piping bag.
Fill each piece of pasta with the mixture.
Beat 3 eggs, add salt, then dip the filled pasta in the egg and cover very well with bread crumbs. Coat twice.
Use a toothpick to check that the oil is hot and fry the pasta.

node.text:
This is the most incredible way to fry an #eggplant!

INGREDIENTS
Eggplants
Salt
Water
Tapioca flour
Oil

METHOD
Peel an eggplant. Cut into large chunks.
Form a grid on each piece without cutting it all together.
Add salt to a bowl with water and place each piece of eggplant and wait for 20 minutes.
Cover each piece with flour. Deep fry with very hot oil.
Serve with sour cream.

node.text:
A simple method to make amazing fluffy #bread!

INGREDIENTS
400ml (1 3/4 cup) Milk
7g dry yeast
2 tbsp sugar
600g (4 cups) Flour
1 tsp salt
30ml (2 1/4 tbsp) Oil
Butter
Apricot jam

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 40 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 pieces.
Boil in hot water for 3 minutes from both sides.
Transfer to the baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 200’C(390’F).
Serve with butter and jam.

node.text:
Kids will love these amazing bi-color #muffins: easy and fluffy! 
 
INGREDIENTS
1 egg
50g sugar
8g vanilla sugar
60ml oil
100ml milk
160g flour
8g baking powder
1 tbsp cacao powder
3 tbsp milk
Almond slices

METHOD
Pour an egg into a bowl, add sugar, vanilla sugar and mix well.
Add oil, milk and mix well.
Mix flour with baking powder and pour into the previous mixture.
Mix cocoa and milk in another bowl. Add half of the mixture to get two different colors.
Pour a little of each mixture into each hole of a muffin tray to make two-color muffins and add almond slices.
Bake for 25 minutes at 180°C (356°F).

node.text:
Beautiful and delicious, these #crepes are just amazing! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
100g (3/4 cup) Flour
230ml (1 cup) water
1 tbsp olive oil
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
8-10 zucchini Flowers
150g baked ham
100g mozzarella cheese

METHOD
In a bowl mix together eggs with salt, pepper, flour, water, oil.
Make pancakes onto the prepared pan and put the flower on top. Fry from both sides.
Fill with baked ham slices and mozzarella slices.

node.text:
The recipe to make amazing #crepes every time!

INGREDIENTS
3 eggs
2g (½ tsp) salt
10g (2 tsp) sugar
125g (1 cup) flour
250ml (1 cup) milk
12ml (1 tbsp) oil
 
Filling:
Honey
Coconut grains
 
METHOD
Add eggs, sugar, salt to the mixing bowl. Whisk with a mixer.
Add milk, oil, and sifted flour. Mix. Rest for 30 minutes.
Bake on an oiled pan.
Serve with coconut grains and honey.

node.text:
These #hashbrowns will be gone in SECONDS!

INGREDIENTS
3 potatoes
1 egg
12g (2 tbsp) cornstarch
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) garlic powder
oil
 
METHOD
Boil the potatoes for 8-10 minutes. Grate the potatoes.
Add egg, starch, salt, and garlic. Mix.
Shape fritters and place them in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Fry in hot oil. Serve.

node.text:
You have never tried an #omelet this tasty!

INGREDIENTS
Red bell pepper
Yellow bell pepper
6 eggs
50g parmesan
Chives
Garlic
Thyme
Extra virgin olive oil
Salt
Pepper
Butter

METHOD
Add minced garlic and oil to a pan. Sprinkle over dried thyme. Cut the peppers, add to the pan, and cook. Then add chives
Pour 6 eggs into a bowl, add Parmesan cheese and mix thoroughly
Add the pepper mixture to the bowl with the egg and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a pan and cook on both sides to get an omelet.

node.text:
These #fritters are so creamy that you will forget your usual pancakes!

INGREDIENTS
250g (1 cup) cottage cheese
10g (2 tsp) vanilla sugar
50g (¼ cup) sugar
180ml (¾ cup) milk
25ml (2 tbsp) oil
2 eggs
150g (1 1/5 cups) flour
5g (1 tsp) baking powder
Apricot jam

METHOD
Add cheese, milk, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla sugar, oil to a mixing bowl. Whisk the mixture. Add flour and baking powder. Stir.
Whisk the egg whites and salt with a mixer and mix with the previous mixture.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Fill with jam. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

node.text:
Cabbage rolls are delicious, have you ever tried them in this way? 😎

INGREDIENTS
500g Chinese cabbage
200g (1.3 cup) minced meat
100g (0.5 cup rice
1 onion
1 yellow bell pepper
1 carrot
Vegetable oil for frying
Garlic
10g (2 tsp) tomato paste
6g (1 tsp) salt
2g (1 tsp) black pepper
Parsley
300ml (10.1oz) tomato sauce

METHOD
Divide the Chinese cabbage into leaves, pour boiling water, cover and leave to stand for 15 minutes.
Pour boiling water over 100 g of rice, cover and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Chop onion, bell pepper, grated the carrot. Heat the oil and add the onion, paprika and carrot. Add the crushed garlic cloves, and then the tomato sauce.
When the vegetables have softened, pour it over the minced meat, then add the softened rice and mix everything.
Fill a cabbage leaf with 1.5 tbsp of a mixture of vegetables, rice and minced meat.
Wrap as shown in the video and place in a baking dish.
When you have filled the baking dish with rolls, sprinkle with tomato sauce.
Cover the parchment with paper and foil.
Bake for 40 minutes at 220°C.

node.text:
Quick and delicious!

INGREDIENTS
220ml (1 cup) yogurt
150g (1 1/4 cup) flour
1 egg
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp soda
1/2 tsp salt
200g minced meat
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
2 tbsp shredded parmesan

METHOD
In a bowl mix together yogurt, egg and spices, add in flour.
In another bowl mix together meat with salt, pepper and Parmesan.
Into the pan on medium heat add a tablespoon of prepared mixture top it with meat and another tablespoon of the mixture.
Fry from both sides.

node.text:
This method is genius! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
 300g (2 cups) all-purpose flour;
 60g (¼ cup) butter, melted;
 100ml (⅓ cup+2 tbsp) water;
 Cornstarch.
 
METHOD
 Combine water, melted butter and flour to form a smooth dough.
 Set the dough aside for 20 minutes then roll into a thin rectangle and dust with cornstarch generously.
 Fold as shown on the video and repeat once more.
 Set the dough aside for 20 minutes then roll out thinly and cut into circles.
 Fold each circle and pinch with a clothing pin. Fry, dipping in hot oil, until the dough ‘blooms’, then remove the toothpick and cook until golden

node.text:
Bread in pan: light and crunchy to prepare in no time! 😍

INGREDIENTS
300g (2 cups) of Flour
5g (1/3 tbsp) of Sugar
7g of dry yeast
2 Eggs
400ml (1 3/4 cup) of warm water
5g (1 teaspoon) of Salt

METHOD
In a bowl add the flour, sugar, yeast, eggs, water and mix them all together until well combined. Let it rest for 1 hour.
Add the salt and mix it all together again.
With a ladle, add the butter to the pan to create a round shape. Cover with a lid and bake on both sides until golden.

node.text:
Ready in a pan in a few minutes! 

INGREDIENTS
1 egg
280g (1 cup) of kefir
6g (1 tsp) of salt
4g (1 tsp) of sugar
25ml (2 tbsp) of vegetable oil
400g (2 1/2 cups) of flour
10g (2 tsp) of baking powder
320g of mozzarella cheese
1 egg
Salt
Pepper
Butter

METHOD
In a bowl add the egg, kefir, salt, sugar, vegetable oil, and whisk. Sift the flour and baking powder and mix all together until well combined.
Knead the dough with your hands, cover with the foil and let it rest for 15 minutes.
In another bowl add the mozzarella cheese, egg, salt, pepper and combine them all together.
Create the balls from the cheese mixture
Divide the dough into 4 equal parts and make balls. Roll out the dough and add a ball of cheese on top. Close the rolled dough on all sides and create a disk shape with your hands.
Cover with a lid and bake on both sides until golden. Finally, coat with butter.

Kids will love this savory treat!

INGREDIENTS
Toast bread
6 hot dogs
Cheese
Butter

METHOD
Freeze toast bread for 3 hours. Cut it into 3 parts.
Cut the hot dogs into 2 parts.
Arrange the bread and hot dogs on a wooden stick. Fry in butter.
Melt the cheese and wrap the skewers in the cheese. Serve.
